<P><TT><B><A NAME="13">13</A></B></TT>  <CITE><U>Ibid.</U></CITE>, Table
A5.
</P>
<P><TT><B><A NAME="14">14</A></B></TT>  A number of communities initiated 
studies to show the costs of implementing  mandates. For example, Michigan
estimated that its  spend
<!-- Generation of PM publication page 3 -->  ing would rise from $39.6 million
to $136.9 million over the sixyear period from  19901995 due to Medicaid
mandates. A 1991  Columbus, Ohio, study reported that the city would  spend $1.1
billion on federal and state environmental mandates over the next ten years, 
consuming nearly 25 percent of the city's budget  by 1996.
</P>
<P><TT><B><A NAME="15">15</A></B></TT>  For a more detailed discussion of 
how regulation destroys jobs, see Laffer, &quot;How  Regulation Is Destroying
American Jobs.&quot;
