enrolls 44 million youngsters, and employs 3 million teachers (and  an equal
number of janitors, cooks, crossing guards, and so on). At the same time, the 
only nationally circulated magazines for and about education (other than union
magazines)  have tiny circulations. The best, <CITE><U>Education  Week</U></CITE>,
hovers around 60,000 subscribers a year.  The AFT's Shanker communicates with
